File.remove 

  bool remove ()

Description 

Deletes the file associated with this object from disk immediately, without moving it to the system
trash.

Does not resolve aliases; instead, deletes the referenced alias or shortcut file itself. Returns true if
the file was successfully removed. IMPORTANT: Cannot be undone. It is recommended that you prompt the
user for permission before deleting.
