  <L=3y#3> toExponential </L>    Converts the Number object to a string in scientific notation.
  readonly                       

  <L=3z#3> toFixed </L> readonly Converts the Number object to a string with fixed decimals.

  <L=3A#2> toLocaleString </L>   Returns the value of a Number object converted to a string, using
  readonly                       localized conventions.

  <L=3B#3> toPrecision </L>      Converts the Number object to a string in either scientific or fixed
  readonly                       notation, epending on its value.

  <L=3C#2> toSource </L>         Creates a string representation of this object that can be fed back
  readonly                       to?eval()?to re-create an object. Works only with built-in classes.

  <L=3D#3> toString </L>         Returns the value of a Number object converted to a string.
  readonly                       

