Object.toString 

  <L=51#6> String </L> toString ()

Description 

Creates and returns a string representing this object.

Many objects (such as?Date) override this method in favor of their own implementation. If an object has
no string value and no user-defined toString() method, the default method returns [object type],
where?type?is the object type or the name of the constructor function that created the object.
