Socket.close 

  bool close ()

Description 

Terminates the open connection.

Returns true if the connection was closed, false on I/O errors. Deleting the object also closes the
connection, but not until JavaScript garbage-collects the object. The connection might stay open longer
than you wish if you do not close it explicitly.
