String <I=6>
Description 

A character string. Each character is adressable by index.

Properties 

  ------------------------------------------------------------- ------------------------------------------
  <L=5h#2> length </L> readonly                                 The length of the string.

  ------------------------------------------------------------- ------------------------------------------

Constructors 

  ------------------------------------- ------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=52#3> String </L> readonly         Returns a string representation of the value given as an argument.

  ------------------------------------- ------------------------------------------------------------------

Methods 

  --------------------------------- -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=53#3> anchor </L> readonly     Returns a string consisting of this string enclosed in a <a> tag.

  <L=54#2> big </L> readonly        Returns a string consisting of this string enclosed in a <big> tag.

  <L=55#2> blink </L> readonly      Returns a string consisting of this string enclosed in a <blink> tag.

  <L=56#2> bold </L> readonly       Returns a string consisting of this string enclosed in a <b> tag.

  <L=57#3> charAt </L> readonly     Returns the character at the specified index.

  <L=58#3> charCodeAt </L> readonly Returns the Unicode value of the character at the given index.

  <L=59#3> concat </L> readonly     If necessary, converts the one or more given values to strings.

  <L=5a#2> fixed </L> readonly      Returns a string consisting of this string enclosed in a <tt> tag.

  <L=5b#3> fontcolor </L> readonly  Returns a string consisting of this string enclosed in a <font> tag.

  <L=5c#3> fontsize </L> readonly   Returns a string consisting of this string enclosed in a <font> tag.

  <L=5e#3> indexOf </L> readonly    Returns the index within the string of the first occurrence of the
                                    specified string, starting the search at fromIndex if provided.

  <L=5f#2> italics </L> readonly    Returns a string consisting of this string enclosed in a <i> tag.

  <L=5g#3> lastIndexOf </L>         Returns the index within the string of the last occurrence of the
  readonly                          specified value.

  <L=5i#3> link </L> readonly       Returns a string consisting of this string enclosed in a <a> tag.

  <L=5j#3> localeCompare </L>       Performs a localized comparison of two strings.
  readonly                          

  <L=5k#3> match </L> readonly      Matches a string against a regular expression.

  <L=5l#3> replace </L> readonly    

  <L=5m#3> search </L> readonly     

  <L=5n#3> slice </L> readonly      Extracts a substring of the given string and returns it as a new
                                    string.

  <L=5o#2> small </L> readonly      Returns a string consisting of this string enclosed in a <small> tag.

  <L=5p#3> split </L> readonly      Splits a string into a group of substrings, places those strings in an
                                    array, and returns the array.

  <L=5q#2> strike </L> readonly     Returns a string consisting of this string enclosed in a <strike> tag.

  <L=5r#2> sub </L> readonly        Returns a string consisting of this string enclosed in a <sub> tag.

  <L=5s#3> substr </L> readonly     Returns a string containing the characters beginning at the specified
                                    index, start, through the specified number of characters.

  <L=5t#3> substring </L> readonly  Returns a substring of the given string by extracting characters from
                                    indexA up to but not including indexB.

  <L=5u#2> sup </L> readonly        Returns a string consisting of this string enclosed in a <sup> tag.

  <L=5v#2> toLocaleLowerCase </L>   Returns a new string which contains all the characters of the original
  readonly                          string converted to lowercase (localized).

  <L=5w#2> toLocaleUpperCase </L>   Returns a new string which contains all the characters of the original
  readonly                          string converted to uppercase (localized).

  <L=5x#2> toLowerCase </L>         Returns a new string which contains all the characters of the original
  readonly                          string converted to lowercase.

  <L=5y#2> toSource </L> readonly   Creates a string representation of this object that can be fed back
                                    to?eval()?to re-create an object. Works only with built-in classes.

  <L=5z#2> toString </L> readonly   Returns itself.

  <L=5A#2> toUpperCase </L>         Returns a new string which contains all the characters of the original
  readonly                          string converted to uppercase.

  <L=5B#2> valueOf </L> readonly    Returns itself.
  --------------------------------- -----------------------------------------------------------------------

Static Methods 

