String.slice 

  <L=51#6> String </L> slice ( <L=3r#5> Number </L> startSlice , <L=3r#5> Number </L> endSlice )

Parameters 

  ----------------------------- --------------------------------------------------------------------------
  startSlice                    The index at which to begin extraction.

  endSlice                      The index at which to end extraction.
  ----------------------------- --------------------------------------------------------------------------

Description 

Extracts a substring of the given string and returns it as a new string.

The substring begins at startSlice, and includes all characters up to, but not including the character at
the index endSlice. A negative value indexes from the end of the string. For example, a negative value
for startSlice is resolved as: string. length + startSlice. The original string is unchanged. Returns a
substring of characters from the given string, starting at startSlice and ending with endSlice-1.
<I=3>
</B>
=========================================================================================================
