BatchOptions 

Description 

Options to specify when running a Batch command.

Static Properties 

  ----------------------------------- --------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=aN#2> destination </L> readonly  The type of destination for the processed files.

  <L=aO#2> destinationFolder </L>     The folder location for the processed files. Valid only when
  readonly                            ‘destination’ = folder.

  <L=aP#2> errorFile </L> readonly    The file in which to log errors encountered. To display errors on
                                      the screen and stop batch processing when errors occur, leave blank.

  <L=aQ#2> fileNaming </L> readonly   A list of file naming options. Maximum: 6.

  <L=aR#2> macintoshCompatible </L>   If true, the final file names are Macintosh compatible.
  readonly                            

  <L=aS#2> overrideOpen </L> readonly If true, overrides action open commands.

  <L=aT#2> overrideSave </L> readonly If true, overrides save as action steps with the specified
                                      destination.

  <L=aU#2> startingSerial </L>        The starting serial number to use in naming files.
  readonly                            

  <L=aV#2> suppressOpen </L> readonly If true, suppresses file open options dialogs.

  <L=aW#2> suppressProfile </L>       If true, suppresses color profile warnings.
  readonly                            

  <L=aX#2> unixCompatible </L>        If true, the final file names are Unix compatible.
  readonly                            

  <L=aY#2> windowsCompatible </L>     If true, the final file names are Windows compatible.
  readonly                            
  ----------------------------------- --------------------------------------------------------------------
</B>
