ChangeMode.INDEXEDCOLOR 

  int INDEXEDCOLOR

Description 

Indexed color, in which the number of colors in the image is reduced to at most 256, the standard number
of colors supported by the GIF and PNG-8 formats and many multimedia applications.

This conversion reduces file size by deleting color information from the image. To convert to indexed
color, you must start with an image that is 8 bits per channel and in either Grayscale or RGB mode.
<I=2>
</B>
=========================================================================================================
