ColorReductionType 

Description 

The color reduction algorithm.

Static Properties 

  --------------------------- -------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=dZ#2> ADAPTIVE </L>      Samples color from the spectrum appearing most commonly in the image.
  readonly                    

  <L=e0#2> BLACKWHITE </L>    Uses a set palette of colors.
  readonly                    

  <L=e1#2> CUSTOM </L>        Uses a color palette that is created or modified by the user. If you open an
  readonly                    existing GIF or PNG-8 file, it will have a custom color palette.

  <L=e2#2> GRAYSCALE </L>     Uses a set palette of colors.
  readonly                    

  <L=e3#2> MACINTOSH </L>     Uses a set palette of colors.
  readonly                    

  <L=e4#2> PERCEPTUAL </L>    Gives priority to colors for which the human eye has greater sensitivity.
  readonly                    

  <L=e5#2> RESTRICTIVE </L>   Uses the standard 216-color color table common to Windows and Mac OS 8-bit
  readonly                    (256-color or web-safe palette); ensures that no browser dither is applied when
                              the image is displayed using 8-bit color.

  <L=e6#2> SELECTIVE </L>     Gives priority to broad areas of color and the preservation of web colors;
  readonly                    usually produces images with the greatest color integrity.

  <L=e7#2> WINDOWS </L>       Uses a set palette of colors.
  readonly                    
  --------------------------- -------------------------------------------------------------------------------
</B>
