DCS1_SaveOptions 

Description 

Options for saving a document in Photoshop DCS 1.0 format.

Static Properties 

  ---------------------------------------- ---------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=fc#2> DCS </L> readonly               The DCS type.

  <L=fd#2> embedColorProfile </L> readonly If true, the color profile is embedded in the document.

  <L=fe#2> encoding </L> readonly          The type of encoding to use for the document.

  <L=ff#2> halftoneScreen </L> readonly    If true, includes halftone screen.

  <L=fg#2> interpolation </L> readonly     If true, image interpolation is used.

  <L=fh#2> preview </L> readonly           The type of preview.

  <L=fi#2> transferFunction </L> readonly  If true, includes transfer functions in the document to
                                           compensate for dot gain between the image and film.

  <L=fj#2> vectorData </L> readonly        If true, includes vector data. Valid only if the document
                                           contains vector data (un-rasterized text).
  ---------------------------------------- ---------------------------------------------------------------
</B>
