DCS2_SaveOptions 

Description 

Options for saving a document in Photoshop DCS 2.0 format.

Static Properties 

  ---------------------------------------- ---------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=fl#2> DCS </L> readonly               The DCS type.

  <L=fm#2> embedColorProfile </L> readonly If true, the color profile is embedded in the document.

  <L=fn#2> encoding </L> readonly          The type of encoding to use for document.

  <L=fo#2> halftoneScreen </L> readonly    If true, includes halftone screen.

  <L=fp#2> interpolation </L> readonly     If true, image interpolation is used.

  <L=fq#2> multiFileDCS </L> readonly      If true, saves color channels as multiple files.

  <L=fr#2> preview </L> readonly           The type of preview.

  <L=fs#2> spotColors </L> readonly        If true, the spot colors are saved.

  <L=ft#2> transferFunction </L> readonly  If true, includes transfer functions in the document to
                                           compensate for dot gain between the image and film.

  <L=fu#2> vectorData </L> readonly        If true, includes vector data. Valid only if the document
                                           contains vector data (un-rasterized text).
  ---------------------------------------- ---------------------------------------------------------------
</B>
