DocumentMode 

Description 

The document’s color mode.

Static Properties 

  ---------------------------- -------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=gQ#2> BITMAP </L>         Bitmap, which uses one of two color values (black or white) to represent the
  readonly                     pixels in an image.

  <L=gR#2> CMYK </L> readonly  CMYK.

  <L=gS#2> DUOTONE </L>        Duotone mode, which creates monotone, duotone (two-color), tritone
  readonly                     (three-color), and quadtone (four-color) grayscale images using one to four
                               custom inks.

  <L=gT#2> GRAYSCALE </L>      Grayscale.
  readonly                     

  <L=gU#2> INDEXEDCOLOR </L>   Indexed color, in which the number of colors in the image is at most 256, the
  readonly                     standard number of colors supported by the GIF and PNG-8 formats and many
                               multimedia applications.

  <L=gV#2> LAB </L> readonly   Lab.

  <L=gW#2> MULTICHANNEL </L>   Image with multiple color channels.
  readonly                     

  <L=gX#2> RGB </L> readonly   RGB.
  ---------------------------- -------------------------------------------------------------------------------
</B>
