EPSSaveOptions 

Description 

Options for saving a document in EPS format.

Static Properties 

  --------------------------------------- ----------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=iD#2> embedColorProfile </L>         If true, the color profile is embedded in the document.
  readonly                                

  <L=iE#2> encoding </L> readonly         The type of encoding to use for the document.

  <L=iF#2> halftoneScreen </L> readonly   If true, includes the halftone screen.

  <L=iG#2> interpolation </L> readonly    If true, uses image interpolation.

  <L=iH#2> preview </L> readonly          The type of preview.

  <L=iI#2> psColorManagement </L>         If true, uses PostScript color management.
  readonly                                

  <L=iJ#2> transferFunction </L> readonly If true, includes the transfer functions in the document to
                                          compensate for dot gain between the image and film.

  <L=iK#2> transparentWhites </L>         If true, displays white areas as transparent. Valid only for
  readonly                                documents in BitMap mode.

  <L=iL#2> vectorData </L> readonly       If true, includes vector data. Valid only when the document
                                          contains vector data (un-rasterized text).
  --------------------------------------- ----------------------------------------------------------------
</B>
