Layer 

Description 

A layer object.

Layers may contain nested layers, which are called sublayers in the user interface. The layer object
contains all of the page items in the specific layer as elements. Your script can access page items as
elements of either the layer object or the document object.

Properties 

  ------------------------------------ -------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=p4#2> allLocked </L> readonly     If true, the layer’s contents and settings are locked.

  <L=p5#2> blendMode </L> readonly     The mode to use when compositing an object.

  <L=p6#2> bounds </L> readonly        If the Layer is a layer set, this property returns a reference to
                                       the corresponding layer set object.

  <L=p7#2> boundsNoEffects </L>        Bounding rectangle of the Layer not including effects.
  readonly                             

  <L=p9#2> id </L> readonly            The unique ID of this layer.

  <L=pa#2> itemIndex </L> readonly     The layer index sans layer groups, how Photoshop would index them.

  <L=pc#2> linkedLayers </L> readonly  The layers linked to this layer.

  <L=pf#2> name </L> readonly          The name of the layer.

  <L=pg#2> opacity </L> readonly       The layer’s master opacity (as a percentage). Range: 0.0 to 100.0.

  <L=ph#2> parent </L> readonly        The object’s container.

  <L=pn#2> typename </L> readonly      The class name of the object.

  <L=pp#2> visible </L> readonly       If true, the layer is visible.

  <L=pq#2> xmpMetadata </L> readonly   XMP metadata associated with the Layer.
  ------------------------------------ -------------------------------------------------------------------

Methods 

  ----------------------------------------------- --------------------------------------------------------
  <L=p8#3> duplicate </L> readonly                Duplicate this object.

  <L=pb#3> link </L> readonly                     Links the layer with the specified layer.

  <L=pd#3> move </L> readonly                     Move the object.

  <L=pe#3> moveToEnd </L> readonly                …

  <L=pi#2> remove </L> readonly                   Deletes this object.

  <L=pj#2> removeAll </L> readonly                Deletes all elements.

  <L=pk#3> resize </L> readonly                   Scales the object.

  <L=pl#3> rotate </L> readonly                   Rotates the object.

  <L=pm#3> translate </L> readonly                Moves the object relative to its current position.

  <L=po#2> unlink </L> readonly                   Unlinks the layer.
  ----------------------------------------------- --------------------------------------------------------
</B>
=========================================================================================================
