OffsetUndefinedAreas 

Description 

The method to use to fill the empty space left by offsetting a an image or selection.

Static Properties 

  ---------------------------------- ---------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=qC#2> REPEATEDGEPIXELS </L>     Extends the colors of pixels along the edge of the image in the
  readonly                           direction specified. Banding may result if the edge pixels are
                                     different colors.

  <L=qD#2> SETTOBACKGROUND </L>      For background layers, sets pixels to the background layer color. For
  readonly                           nonbackground layers, sets the pixels to transparent.

  <L=qE#2> WRAPAROUND </L> readonly  Fills the undefined space with content from the opposite edge of the
                                     image.
  ---------------------------------- ---------------------------------------------------------------------
</B>
=========================================================================================================
