PDFResampleType 

Description 

Downsampling options when saving as PDF.

Static Properties 

  ---------------------------- ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=rO#2> NONE </L> readonly  Does not downsample.

  <L=rP#2> PDFAVERAGE </L>     Averages the pixels in a sample area and replaces the entire area with the
  readonly                     average pixel color at the specified resolution.

  <L=rQ#2> PDFBICUBIC </L>     Uses a weighted average to determine pixel color, which usually yields better
  readonly                     results than the simple averaging method of downsampling. The slowest but most
                               precise method, resulting in the smoothest gradations.

  <L=rR#2> PDFSUBSAMPLE </L>   Chooses a pixel in the center of the sample area and replaces the entire area
  readonly                     with that pixel color; significantly reduces conversion time but results in
                               images that are less smooth and continuous.
  ---------------------------- ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
</B>
=========================================================================================================
