PaletteType 

Description 

The palette type for converting an image to indexed color.

Static Properties 

  -------------------------------- -------------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=t2#2> EXACT </L> readonly     The palette uses the exact colors appearing in the RGB image; available
                                   only if the image uses 256 or fewer colors.

  <L=t3#2> LOCALADAPTIVE </L>      Creates a palette by sampling the colors from the spectrum appearing most
  readonly                         commonly in the image.

  <L=t4#2> LOCALPERCEPTUAL </L>    Creates a custom palette by giving priority to colors for in the image
  readonly                         which the human eye has greater sensitivity.

  <L=t5#2> LOCALSELECTIVE </L>     Creates a color table similar to the Perceptual color table, but favoring
  readonly                         broad areas of color in the image and the preservation of web colors.

  <L=t6#2> MACOSPALETTE </L>       The Mac OS default 8-bit palette, whch is based on a uniform sampling of
  readonly                         RGB colors.

  <L=t7#2> MASTERADAPTIVE </L>     Creates a palette by sampling the colors from the spectrum appearing most
  readonly                         commonly in a group of open images that share the same color palette.

  <L=t8#2> MASTERPERCEPTUAL </L>   Creates a custom palette by giving priority to colors in a group of open
  readonly                         images with the same color palette for which the human eye has greater
                                   sensitivity.

  <L=t9#2> MASTERSELECTIVE </L>    Creates a color table similar to the Master Perceptual color table, but
  readonly                         favoring broad areas of color and the preservation of web colors.

  <L=ta#2> PREVIOUSPALETTE </L>    Uses the custom palette from the previous conversion, making it easy to
  readonly                         convert several images with the same custom palette.

  <L=tb#2> UNIFORM </L> readonly   Creates a palette by uniformly sampling colors from the RGB color cube.

  <L=tc#2> WEBPALETTE </L>         The 216-color palette that web browsers, regardless of platform, use to
  readonly                         display images on a monitor limited to 256 colors.

  <L=td#2> WINDOWSPALETTE </L>     The Windows system’s default 8-bit palette, whch is based on a uniform
  readonly                         sampling of RGB colors.
  -------------------------------- -------------------------------------------------------------------------
</B>
=========================================================================================================
