TextComposer.ADOBEEVERYLINE 

  int ADOBEEVERYLINE

Description 

Considers a network of break points for a range of lines and thus optimizes earlier lines in the
paragraph to eliminate especially unattractive breaks later on. Results in more even spacing and fewer
hyphens.

The Adobe Every-line composer approaches composition by identifying possible breakpoints, evaluating
them, and assigning a weighted penalty based on these principles: Highest importance is given to evenness
of letter and word spacing; Possible breakpoints are evaluated and penalized according to how much they
deviate from optimal spacing; Hyphenation is avoided when possible; Breakpoints that require hyphenation
are penalized more than those that create uneven spacing; Good breakpoints are preferred over bad
breakpoints.
<I=2>
</B>
=========================================================================================================
