TiffEncodingType 

Description 

The encoding to use when saving to TIFF format.

Static Properties 

  --------------------------------- ----------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=B2#2> JPEG </L> readonly       JPEG compression, which is lossy and recommended for continuous-tone
                                    images, such as photographs.

  <L=B3#2> NONE </L> readonly       No compression.

  <L=B4#2> TIFFLZW </L> readonly    LZW compression, which is lossless and most useful for images with
                                    large areas of single color.

  <L=B5#2> TIFFZIP </L> readonly    Zip compression, which is lossless and most effective for images that
                                    contain large areas of single color.
  --------------------------------- ----------------------------------------------------------------------
</B>
=========================================================================================================
