EditText 

Description 

An editable text field that the user can select and change.

Calls the?onChange()?callback if the text is changed and the user types Enter or the control loses focus,
or if its?notify()?method is called. Calls the?onChanging()?callback when any change is made to the text.
The?textselection?property contains currently selected text.

Properties 

  ------------------------------- ------------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=Fi#2> active </L> readonly   True if this element is active.

  <L=Fk#2> alignment </L>         The alignment style for this element. If defined, this value overrides
  readonly                        the alignChildren setting for the parent container.

  <L=Fl#2> bounds </L> readonly   The boundaries of the element, in parent-relative coordinates.

  <L=Fm#2> characters </L>        A number of characters for which to reserve space when calculating the
  readonly                        preferred size of the element.

  <L=Fn#2> children </L> readonly An array of child elements.

  <L=Fp#2> enabled </L> readonly  True if this element is enabled.

  <L=Fq#2> graphics </L> readonly The graphics object that can be used to customize the element’s
                                  appearance, in response to the?onDraw()?event.

  <L=Fr#2> helpTip </L> readonly  The help text that is displayed when the mouse hovers over the element.

  <L=Ft#2> indent </L> readonly   The number of pixels to indent the element during automatic layout.

  <L=Fu#2> justify </L> readonly  The text justification style.

  <L=Fv#2> location </L> readonly The upper left corner of this element relative to its parent.

  <L=Fw#2> maximumSize </L>       The maximum height and width to which the element can be resized.
  readonly                        

  <L=Fx#2> minimumSize </L>       The minimum height and width to which the element can be resized.
  readonly                        

  <L=FF#2> parent </L> readonly   The parent element.

  <L=FG#2> preferredSize </L>     The preferred size, used by layout managers to determine the best size
  readonly                        for each element.

  <L=FH#2> properties </L>        An object that contains one or more creation properties of the container
  readonly                        (properties used only when the element is created).

  <L=FJ#2> shortcutKey </L>       The key sequence that invokes the?onShortcutKey()?callback for this
  readonly                        element (in Windows only).

  <L=FL#2> size </L> readonly     The current dimensions of this element.

  <L=FM#2> text </L> readonly     The current text displayed in the field, a localizable string.

  <L=FN#2> textselection </L>     The currently selected text, or the empty string if there is no text
  readonly                        selected.

  <L=FO#2> type </L> readonly     The element type; “edittext”.

  <L=FP#2> visible </L> readonly  True if this element is shown, false if it is hidden.

  <L=FQ#2> window </L> readonly   The window that this element belongs to.

  <L=FR#2> windowBounds </L>      The bounds of this element relative to the top-level parent window.
  readonly                        
  ------------------------------- ------------------------------------------------------------------------

Methods 

  --------------------------------------------- ----------------------------------------------------------
  <L=Fj#3> addEventListener </L> readonly       Registers an event handler for a particular type of event
                                                occuring in this element.

  <L=Fo#2> dispatchEvent </L> readonly          Simulates the occurrence of an event in this target.

  <L=Fs#2> hide </L> readonly                   Hides this element.

  <L=Fy#3> notify </L> readonly                 Sends a notification message, simulating the specified
                                                user interaction event.

  <L=FI#3> removeEventListener </L> readonly    Unregisters an event handler for a particular type of
                                                event occuring in this element.

  <L=FK#2> show </L> readonly                   Shows this element.
  --------------------------------------------- ----------------------------------------------------------

Events 

  --------------------------------- ----------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=Fz#2> onActivate </L> readonly An event-handler callback function, called when the element acquires
                                    the keyboard focus.

  <L=FA#2> onChange </L> readonly   An event-handler callback function, called when the content of the
                                    element has been changed

  <L=FB#2> onChanging </L> readonly An event-handler callback function, called when the content of the
                                    element is in the process of changing

  <L=FC#2> onDeactivate </L>        An event-handler callback function, called when the element loses the
  readonly                          keyboard focus.

  <L=FD#2> onDraw </L> readonly     An event-handler callback function, called when the window is about to
                                    be drawn.

  <L=FE#2> onShortcutKey </L>       An event-handler callback function, called when the
  readonly                          element’s?shortcutKey?sequence is typed in the active window.
  --------------------------------- ----------------------------------------------------------------------
</B>
