Event 

Description 

Base class for UIEvent.

Encapsulates input event information for an event that propagates through a container and control
hierarchy. Implements W3C standard event handling.

Properties 

  ----------------------------- ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=G1#2> bubbles </L>         True if the event is of a type that bubbles.
  readonly                      

  <L=G2#2> cancelable </L>      True if the default action associated with the event can be canceled with
  readonly                      preventDefault().

  <L=G3#2> captures </L>        True if this event can be captured.
  readonly                      

  <L=G4#2> currentTarget </L>   The event target object which is currently handling the event. During
  readonly                      capturing and bubbling, this is different from the property target.

  <L=G5#2> eventPhase </L>      The current phase of event propagation; one of none, target, capture,
  readonly                      bubble.

  <L=G8#2> target </L> readonly The event target object for this event.

  <L=G9#2> timeStamp </L>       The date and time at which the event occurred.
  readonly                      

  <L=Ga#2> type </L> readonly   The name of the event that this object represents.
  ----------------------------- ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Static Properties 

  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- ---
  <L=FX#2> AT_TARGET </L> readonly                                                                     

  <L=FY#2> BUBBLING_PHASE </L> readonly                                                                

  <L=FZ#2> CAPTURING_PHASE </L> readonly                                                               

  <L=G0#2> NOT_DISPATCHING </L> readonly                                                               
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- ---

Methods 

  -------------------------------------------- -----------------------------------------------------------
  <L=G6#2> preventDefault </L> readonly        Prevents the default action associated with this event from
                                               being called.

  <L=G7#2> stopPropagation </L> readonly       Stops the propagation of this event.
