Panel.spacing 

  <L=3r#5> Number </L> spacing

Description 

The number of pixels separating one child element from its adjacent sibling element.

Because each container holds only a single row or column of children, only a single spacing value is
needed for a container. The default value is based on the type of container, and is chosen to match
standard Adobe UI guidelines.
