ScriptUI 

Description 

A global class containing central information about ScriptUI. Not instantiable.

Static Properties 

  ---------------------------------- ---------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=L8#2> Alignment </L> readonly   Collects the enumerated values that can be used in the alignment and
                                     alignChildren properties of controls and containers.

  <L=L9#2> FontStyle </L> readonly   Collects the enumerated values that can be used as the style argument
                                     to the?ScriptUI.newFont()?method.

  <L=La#2> applicationFonts </L>     The font constants defined by the host application.
  readonly                           

  <L=Lb#2> compatibility </L>        An object whose properties are the names of compatability modes
  readonly                           supported by the host application.

  <L=Lc#2> coreVersion </L> readonly A string containing the internal version number of the ScriptUI
                                     module.

  <L=Ld#2> environment </L> readonly An object whose properties define attributes of the environment in
                                     which ScriptUI operates.

  <L=Le#2> events </L> readonly      An object whose properties and methods provide access to objects used
                                     in the ScriptUI event system.

  <L=Lf#2> frameworkName </L>        A string containing the name of the UI component framework with which
  readonly                           this version of ScriptUI is compatible.

  <L=Lj#2> version </L> readonly     A string containing the version number of the ScriptUI component
                                     framework
  ---------------------------------- ---------------------------------------------------------------------

Static Methods 

  -------------------------------------- -----------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=Lg#3> getResourceText </L> readonly Finds and returns the resource for a given text string from the
                                         host application’s resource data.

  <L=Lh#3> newFont </L> readonly         Creates a new font object for use in text controls and titles.

  <L=Li#3> newImage </L> readonly        Loads a new image from resources or disk files into an image
                                         object.
  -------------------------------------- -----------------------------------------------------------------
