ScriptUIGraphics 

Description 

An object used to draw custom graphics, found in the graphics property of window, container, and control
objects.

Allows a script to customize aspects of the element?s appearance, such as the color and font. Use an
onDraw callback function to set these properties or call the functions.All measurements are in pixels.

Properties 

  ------------------------------------------- ------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=KB#2> backgroundColor </L> readonly      The background color for containers; for non-containers, the
                                              parent background color.

  <L=KD#2> currentPath </L> readonly          The current drawing path, encapsulated in a path object.

  <L=KE#2> currentPoint </L> readonly         The current position in the current drawing path.

  <L=KF#2> disabledBackgroundColor </L>       The background color for containers when disabled or
  readonly                                    inactive; for non-containers, the parent background color.

  <L=KG#2> disabledForegroundColor </L>       The text color when the element is disabled or inactive.
  readonly                                    

  <L=KN#2> font </L> readonly                 The default font to use for displaying text.

  <L=KO#2> foregroundColor </L> readonly      The text color.
  ------------------------------------------- ------------------------------------------------------------

Static Properties 

  -------------------------------------------- -----------------------------------------------------------
  <L=Kz#2> BrushType </L> readonly             Contains the enumerated constants for the type argument
                                               of?newBrush().

  <L=KA#2> PenType </L> readonly               Contains the enumerated constants for the type argument
                                               of?newPen().
  -------------------------------------------- -----------------------------------------------------------

Methods 

  ------------------------------ -------------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=KC#2> closePath </L>        Closes the current path.
  readonly                       

  <L=KH#3> drawFocusRing </L>    Draws a focus ring within a region of this element.
  readonly                       

  <L=KI#3> drawImage </L>        Draws an image within a given region of the element.
  readonly                       

  <L=KJ#2> drawOSControl </L>    Draw the platform-specific control associated with this element.
  readonly                       

  <L=KK#3> drawString </L>       Draw a string of text starting at a given point in this element, using a
  readonly                       given drawing pen and font.

  <L=KL#3> ellipsePath </L>      Defines an elliptical path within a given rectangular area in
  readonly                       the?currentPath?object, which can be filled using?fillPath()?or stroked
                                 using?strokePath().

  <L=KM#3> fillPath </L>         Fills a path using a given painting brush.
  readonly                       

  <L=KP#3> lineTo </L> readonly  Adds a path segment to the?currentPath.

  <L=KQ#3> measureString </L>    Calculates the size needed to display a string using the given font.
  readonly                       

  <L=KR#3> moveTo </L> readonly  Adds a given point to the?currentPath, and makes it the current drawing
                                 position.

  <L=KS#3> newBrush </L>         Creates a new painting brush object.
  readonly                       

  <L=KT#2> newPath </L> readonly Creates a new, empty path object.

  <L=KU#3> newPen </L> readonly  Creates a new drawing pen object.

  <L=KV#3> rectPath </L>         Defines a rectangular path in the?currentPath?object.
  readonly                       

  <L=KW#3> strokePath </L>       Strokes the path segments of a path with a given drawing pen.
  readonly                       
  ------------------------------ -------------------------------------------------------------------------
</B>
