<B=Lk>Scrollbar
& Scrollbar &
 ____                 _ _ _                
/ ___|  ___ _ __ ___ | | | |__   __ _ _ __ 
\___ \ / __| '__/ _ \| | | '_ \ / _` | '__|
 ___) | (__| | | (_) | | | |_) | (_| | |   
|____/ \___|_|  \___/|_|_|_.__/ \__,_|_|   
                                           
Scrollbar 

Description 

A scrollbar with a draggable scroll indicator and stepper buttons to move the indicator.

The scrollbar control has a horizontal orientation if the width is greater than the height at creation
time, or vertical if its height is greater than its width. Calls the?onChange()?callback after the
position of the indicator is changed or if its?notify()?method is called. Calls the?onChanging()?callback
repeatedly while the user is moving the indicator. Scrollbars are often created with an
associated?EditText?field to display the current value of the scrollbar, and to allow setting the
scrollbar’s position to a specific value.

Properties 

  ------------------------------- ------------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=Ll#2> active </L> readonly   True if this element is active.

  <L=Ln#2> alignment </L>         The alignment style for this element. If defined, this value overrides
  readonly                        the alignChildren setting for the parent container.

  <L=Lo#2> bounds </L> readonly   The boundaries of the element, in parent-relative coordinates.

  <L=Lp#2> children </L> readonly An array of child elements.

  <L=Lr#2> enabled </L> readonly  True if this element is enabled.

  <L=Ls#2> graphics </L> readonly The graphics object that can be used to customize the element’s
                                  appearance, in response to the?onDraw()?event.

  <L=Lt#2> helpTip </L> readonly  The help text that is displayed when the mouse hovers over the element.

  <L=Lv#2> indent </L> readonly   The number of pixels to indent the element during automatic layout.

  <L=Lw#2> jumpdelta </L>         The amount to increment or decrement a scrollbar indicator’s position
  readonly                        when the user clicks ahead or behind the moveable element.

  <L=Lx#2> location </L> readonly The upper left corner of this element relative to its parent.

  <L=Ly#2> maximumSize </L>       The maximum height and width to which the element can be resized.
  readonly                        

  <L=Lz#2> maxvalue </L> readonly The maximum value allowed in the value property.

  <L=LA#2> minimumSize </L>       The minimum height and width to which the element can be resized.
  readonly                        

  <L=LB#2> minvalue </L> readonly The minimum value allowed in the value property.

  <L=LJ#2> parent </L> readonly   The parent element.

  <L=LK#2> preferredSize </L>     The preferred size, used by layout managers to determine the best size
  readonly                        for each element.

  <L=LL#2> properties </L>        An object that contains one or more creation properties of the container
  readonly                        (properties used only when the element is created).

  <L=LN#2> shortcutKey </L>       The key sequence that invokes the ?onShortcutKey()?callback for this
  readonly                        element (in Windows only).

  <L=LP#2> size </L> readonly     The current dimensions of this element.

  <L=LQ#2> stepdelta </L>         The amount by which to increment or decrement a scrollbar element’s
  readonly                        position when the user clicks a stepper button.

  <L=LR#2> type </L> readonly     The element type, “scrollbar”.

  <L=LS#2> value </L> readonly    The current position of the indicator.

  <L=LT#2> visible </L> readonly  True if this element is shown, false if it is hidden.

  <L=LU#2> window </L> readonly   The window that this element belongs to.

  <L=LV#2> windowBounds </L>      The bounds of this element relative to the top-level parent window.
  readonly                        
  ------------------------------- ------------------------------------------------------------------------

Methods 

  --------------------------------------------- ----------------------------------------------------------
  <L=Lm#3> addEventListener </L> readonly       Registers an event handler for a particular type of event
                                                occuring in this element.

  <L=Lq#2> dispatchEvent </L> readonly          Simulates the occurrence of an event in this target.

  <L=Lu#2> hide </L> readonly                   Hides this element.

  <L=LC#3> notify </L> readonly                 Sends a notification message, simulating the specified
                                                user interaction event.

  <L=LM#3> removeEventListener </L> readonly    Unregisters an event handler for a particular type of
                                                event occuring in this element.

  <L=LO#2> show </L> readonly                   Shows this element.
  --------------------------------------------- ----------------------------------------------------------

Events 

  ------------------------------- ------------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=LD#2> onActivate </L>        An event-handler callback function, called when the element acquires the
  readonly                        keyboard focus.

  <L=LE#2> onChange </L> readonly An event-handler callback function, called when the user has finished
                                  dragging the position indicator, or has clicked the control.

  <L=LF#2> onChanging </L>        An event-handler callback function, called when the content of the
  readonly                        element is in the process of changing

  <L=LG#2> onDeactivate </L>      An event-handler callback function, called when the element loses the
  readonly                        keyboard focus.

  <L=LH#2> onDraw </L> readonly   An event-handler callback function, called when the window is about to
                                  be drawn.

  <L=LI#2> onShortcutKey </L>     An event-handler callback function, called when the
  readonly                        element’s?shortcutKey?sequence is typed in the active window.
  ------------------------------- ------------------------------------------------------------------------
</B>
