<B=LW>Slider
& Slider &
 ____  _ _     _           
/ ___|| (_) __| | ___ _ __ 
\___ \| | |/ _` |/ _ \ '__|
 ___) | | | (_| |  __/ |   
|____/|_|_|\__,_|\___|_|   
                           
Slider 

Description 

A slider bar that indicates a numeric value with a moveable position indicator.

All slider controls have a horizontal orientation. Calls the?onChange()?callback after the position of
the indicator is changed or if its?notify()?method is called. Calls the?onChanging()?callback repeatedly
while the user is moving the indicator. The?value?property contains the current position of the indicator
within the range of?minvalue?to?maxvalue.

Properties 

  ------------------------------- ------------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=LX#2> active </L> readonly   True if this element is active.

  <L=LZ#2> alignment </L>         The alignment style for this element. If defined, this value overrides
  readonly                        the alignChildren setting for the parent container.

  <L=M0#2> bounds </L> readonly   The boundaries of the element, in parent-relative coordinates.

  <L=M1#2> children </L> readonly An array of child elements.

  <L=M3#2> enabled </L> readonly  True if this element is enabled.

  <L=M4#2> graphics </L> readonly The graphics object that can be used to customize the element’s
                                  appearance, in response to the?onDraw()?event.

  <L=M5#2> helpTip </L> readonly  The help text that is displayed when the mouse hovers over the element.

  <L=M7#2> indent </L> readonly   The number of pixels to indent the element during automatic layout.

  <L=M8#2> location </L> readonly The upper left corner of this element relative to its parent.

  <L=M9#2> maximumSize </L>       The maximum height and width to which the element can be resized.
  readonly                        

  <L=Ma#2> maxvalue </L> readonly The maximum value allowed in the?value?property.

  <L=Mb#2> minimumSize </L>       The minimum height and width to which the element can be resized.
  readonly                        

  <L=Mc#2> minvalue </L> readonly The minimum value allowed in the?value?property.

  <L=Mk#2> parent </L> readonly   The parent element.

  <L=Ml#2> preferredSize </L>     The preferred size, used by layout managers to determine the best size
  readonly                        for each element.

  <L=Mm#2> properties </L>        An object that contains one or more creation properties of the container
  readonly                        (properties used only when the element is created).

  <L=Mo#2> shortcutKey </L>       The key sequence that invokes the?onShortcutKey()?callback for this
  readonly                        element (in Windows only).

  <L=Mq#2> size </L> readonly     The current dimensions of this element.

  <L=Mr#2> type </L> readonly     The element type, “slider”.

  <L=Ms#2> value </L> readonly    The current position of the indicator.

  <L=Mt#2> visible </L> readonly  True if this element is shown, false if it is hidden.

  <L=Mu#2> window </L> readonly   The window that this element belongs to.

  <L=Mv#2> windowBounds </L>      The bounds of this element relative to the top-level parent window.
  readonly                        
  ------------------------------- ------------------------------------------------------------------------

Methods 

  -------------------------------------------- -----------------------------------------------------------
  <L=LY#3> addEventListener </L> readonly      Registers an event handler for a particular type of event
                                               occuring in this element.

  <L=M2#2> dispatchEvent </L> readonly         Simulates the occurrence of an event in this target.

  <L=M6#2> hide </L> readonly                  Hides this element.

  <L=Md#3> notify </L> readonly                Sends a notification message, simulating the specified user
                                               interaction event.

  <L=Mn#3> removeEventListener </L> readonly   Unregisters an event handler for a particular type of event
                                               occuring in this element.

  <L=Mp#2> show </L> readonly                  Shows this element.
  -------------------------------------------- -----------------------------------------------------------

Events 

  ------------------------------ -------------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=Me#2> onActivate </L>       An event-handler callback function, called when the element acquires the
  readonly                       keyboard focus.

  <L=Mf#2> onChange </L>         An event-handler callback function, called when the user has finished
  readonly                       dragging the position indicator, or has clicked the control.

  <L=Mg#2> onChanging </L>       An event-handler callback function, called when the content of the
  readonly                       element is in the process of changing

  <L=Mh#2> onDeactivate </L>     An event-handler callback function, called when the element loses the
  readonly                       keyboard focus.

  <L=Mi#2> onDraw </L> readonly  An event-handler callback function, called when the window is about to be
                                 drawn.

  <L=Mj#2> onShortcutKey </L>    An event-handler callback function, called when the
  readonly                       element’s?shortcutKey?sequence is typed in the active window.
  ------------------------------ -------------------------------------------------------------------------
