UIEvent <I=5>
Description 

Encapsulates input event information for an event that propagates through a container and control
hierarchy.

Implements W3C standard event handling. This object is passed to a function that you register to respond
to events of a certain type that occur in a window or control. Use windowObj.addEventListener()?or
controlObj.addEventListener() to register a handler function.

Properties 

  ----------------------------- --------------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=NJ#2> bubbles </L>         True if the event is of a type that bubbles.
  readonly                      

  <L=NK#2> cancelable </L>      True if the default action associated with the event can be canceled with
  readonly                      preventDefault().

  <L=NL#2> captures </L>        True if this event can be captured.
  readonly                      

  <L=NM#2> currentTarget </L>   The event target object which is currently handling the event. During
  readonly                      capturing and bubbling, this is different from the property target.

  <L=NN#2> detail </L> readonly The click count for a mouse-click event.

  <L=NO#2> eventPhase </L>      The current phase of event propagation; one of none, target, capture,
  readonly                      bubble.

  <L=NT#2> target </L> readonly The event target object for this event.

  <L=NU#2> timeStamp </L>       The date and time at which the event occurred.
  readonly                      

  <L=NV#2> type </L> readonly   The name of the event that this object represents.

  <L=NW#2> view </L> readonly   The ScriptUI element that this event relates to.
  ----------------------------- --------------------------------------------------------------------------

Constructors 

  ----------------------------------------------------------------------- --------------------------------
  <L=NI#3> UIEvent </L> readonly                                          Creates an event.

  ----------------------------------------------------------------------- --------------------------------

Methods 

  --------------------------------------------- ----------------------------------------------------------
  <L=NP#3> initEvent </L> readonly              Initializes a UI event as a core W3C event.

  <L=NQ#3> initUIEvent </L> readonly            Initializes an event.

  <L=NR#2> preventDefault </L> readonly         Prevents the default action associated with this event
                                                from being called.

  <L=NS#2> stopPropagation </L> readonly        Stops the propagation of this event.
  --------------------------------------------- ----------------------------------------------------------
<I=5>
</B>
