Window 

Description 

The instance represents a top-level window or dialog box, which contains user-interface elements.

The globally available?Window?object provides access to predefined and script-defined windows.

Properties 

  ------------------------------ --------------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=NY#2> active </L> readonly  Set to true to make this window active.

  <L=O2#2> alignChildren </L>    Tells the layout manager how unlike-sized children of this container
  readonly                       should be aligned within a column or row.

  <L=O3#2> alignment </L>        The alignment style for child elements of a container. If defined, this
  readonly                       value overrides the alignChildren setting for the parent container.

  <L=O4#2> bounds </L> readonly  The bounds of the window’s drawable area, excluding the frame, in screen
                                 coordinates.

  <L=O5#2> cancelElement </L>    For windows of type dialog, the UI element to notify when the user presses
  readonly                       a cancellation key combination.

  <L=O7#2> characters </L>       A number of characters for which to reserve space when calculating the
  readonly                       preferred size of the window.

  <L=O8#2> children </L>         The collection of UI elements that have been added to this container.
  readonly                       

  <L=Ob#2> defaultElement </L>   For windows of type dialog, the UI element to notify when the user presses
  readonly                       a Enter key.

  <L=Od#2> enabled </L> readonly True if this element is enabled.

  <L=Of#2> frameBounds </L>      The bounds of the window frame in screen coordinates.
  readonly                       

  <L=Og#2> frameLocation </L>    The top left corner of the window frame in screen coordinates.
  readonly                       

  <L=Oh#2> frameSize </L>        The size and location of the window’s frame in screen coordinates.
  readonly                       

  <L=Oj#2> graphics </L>         The graphics object that can be used to customize the window?s appearance,
  readonly                       in response to the onDraw event.

  <L=Ok#2> helpTip </L> readonly The help text that is displayed when the mouse hovers over the element.

  <L=Om#2> indent </L> readonly  The number of pixels to indent the element.

  <L=On#2> justify </L> readonly The default text justification style for child text elements.

  <L=Oo#2> layout </L> readonly  The layout manager for this container.

  <L=Op#2> location </L>         The upper left corner of the window’s drawable area.
  readonly                       

  <L=Oq#2> margins </L> readonly The number of pixels between the edges of a container and the outermost
                                 child elements.

  <L=Or#2> maximized </L>        True if the window is expanded.
  readonly                       

  <L=Os#2> maximumSize </L>      The largest rectangle to which the window can be resized.
  readonly                       

  <L=Ot#2> minimized </L>        True if the window is minimized or iconified.
  readonly                       

  <L=Ou#2> minimumSize </L>      The smallest rectangle to which the window can be resized.
  readonly                       

  <L=OF#2> opacity </L> readonly The opacity of the window, in the range [0..1].

  <L=OG#2> orientation </L>      The layout orientation of children in a container.
  readonly                       

  <L=OH#2> parent </L> readonly  The immediate parent element.

  <L=OI#2> preferredSize </L>    The preferred size of the window.
  readonly                       

  <L=OK#2> properties </L>       An object that contains one or more creation properties of the container
  readonly                       (properties used only when the element is created).

  <L=ON#2> shortcutKey </L>      The keypress combination that invokes this
  readonly                       element’s?onShortcutKey()?callback.

  <L=OP#2> size </L> readonly    The current size and location of the content area of the window in screen
                                 coordinates.

  <L=OQ#2> spacing </L> readonly The number of pixels separating one child element from its adjacent
                                 sibling element.

  <L=OR#2> text </L> readonly    The title, label, or displayed text, a localizeable string.

  <L=OS#2> type </L> readonly    The element type; “dialog”, “palette”, or “window”.

  <L=OU#2> visible </L> readonly When true, the element is shown, when false it is hidden.

  <L=OV#3> window </L> readonly  The window that this element belongs to.

  <L=OW#2> windowBounds </L>     The bounds of this window relative to the top-level parent window.
  readonly                       
  ------------------------------ --------------------------------------------------------------------------

Static Properties 

  ------------------------------------------------------ -------------------------------------------------
  <L=Oi#2> frameworkName </L> readonly                   Deprecated. Use?ScriptUI.frameworkName?instead.

  <L=OT#2> version </L> readonly                         Deprecated. Use?ScriptUI.version?instead.
  ------------------------------------------------------ -------------------------------------------------

Constructors 

  ----------------------------------------------------------------- --------------------------------------
  <L=OV#3> Window </L> readonly                                     Creates a new window.

  ----------------------------------------------------------------- --------------------------------------

Methods 

  ----------------------------------------- --------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=NZ#3> add </L> readonly                Creates and returns a new control or container object and adds
                                            it to the children of this window.

  <L=O0#3> addEventListener </L> readonly   Registers an event handler for a particular type of event
                                            occuring in this window.

  <L=O6#3> center </L> readonly             Centers this window on screen or with repect to another
                                            window.

  <L=O9#3> close </L> readonly              Closes this window.

  <L=Oc#2> dispatchEvent </L> readonly      Simulates the occurrence of an event in this target.

  <L=Ol#2> hide </L> readonly               Hides this windows.

  <L=Ov#3> notify </L> readonly             Sends a notification message to all listeners, simulating the
                                            specified user interaction event.

  <L=OL#3> remove </L> readonly             Removes the specified child control from this window?s
                                            children array.

  <L=OM#3> removeEventListener </L>         Unregisters an event handler for a particular type of event
  readonly                                  occuring in this window.

  <L=OO#2> show </L> readonly               Makes this window visible.
  ----------------------------------------- --------------------------------------------------------------

Static Methods 

  ------------------------------ -------------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=O1#3> alert </L> readonly   Displays a platform-standard dialog containing a short message and an OK
                                 button.

  <L=Oa#3> confirm </L> readonly Displays a platform-standard dialog containing a short message and two
                                 buttons labeled Yes and No.

  <L=Oe#3> find </L> readonly    Use this method to find an existing window.

  <L=OJ#3> prompt </L> readonly  Displays a modal dialog that returns the user?s text input.
  ------------------------------ -------------------------------------------------------------------------

Events 

  ----------------------------- ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  <L=Ow#2> onActivate </L>      An event-handler callback function, called when the window acquires the
  readonly                      keyboard focus.

  <L=Ox#2> onClose </L>         An event-handler callback function, called when the window is about to be
  readonly                      closed.

  <L=Oy#2> onDeactivate </L>    An event-handler callback function, called when the window loses the
  readonly                      keyboard focus.

  <L=Oz#2> onMove </L> readonly An event-handler callback function, called when the window has been moved

  <L=OA#2> onMoving </L>        An event-handler callback function, called when the window is being moved
  readonly                      

  <L=OB#2> onResize </L>        An event-handler callback function, called after the window has been
  readonly                      resized

  <L=OC#2> onResizing </L>      An event-handler callback function, called while a window is being resized
  readonly                      

  <L=OD#2> onShortcutKey </L>   In Windows only, an event-handler callback function, called a shortcut-key
  readonly                      sequence is typed that matches the?shortcutKey?value for this window.

  <L=OE#2> onShow </L> readonly An event-handler callback function, called just before the window is
                                displayed
  ----------------------------- ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
