Window.find 

  Window find ( <L=51#6> String </L> type , <L=51#6> String </L> title )

Parameters 

  --------- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  type      The name of a predefined resource available to JavaScript in the current application; or the
            window type.

  title     The window title.
  --------- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Description 

Use this method to find an existing window.

This includes windows defined by ScriptUI resource strings, windows already created by a script, and
windows created by the application (if the application supports this case). This function is not
supported by all applications. Returns a?Window?object found or generated from the resource, or null if
no such window or resource exists.
<I=3>
</B>
