Window.onClose 

  Boolean onClose ()

Description 

An event-handler callback function, called when the window is about to be closed.

Called when a request is made to close the window, either by an explicit call to the?close()?function or
by a user action (clicking the OS-specific close icon in the title bar). The function is called before
the window actually closes; it can return false to cancel the close operation.
<I=2>
</B>
